<p><i><b>L'arma l'ora il movente</b></i>, internationally released as <i><b>The Weapon, the Hour, &amp; the Motive</b></i>, is a 1972 <a href="/wiki/Cinema_of_Italy" title="Cinema of Italy">Italian</a> <a href="/wiki/Giallo" title="Giallo">giallo</a> film directed by <a href="/w/index.php?title=Francesco_Mazzei&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Francesco Mazzei (page does not exist)">Francesco Mazzei</a>. It is the first giallo that shows a corrupt priest as victim of a crime, a plot that would become a <a href="/wiki/Topos" title="Topos">topos</a> of the genre.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Cast">Cast</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=The_Weapon,_the_Hour_%26_the_Motive&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Cast">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Renzo_Montagnani" title="Renzo Montagnani">Renzo Montagnani</a>: Inspector Boito</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Bedy_Moratti&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Bedy Moratti (page does not exist)">Bedy Moratti</a>: Orchidea</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Eva_Czemerys" title="Eva Czemerys">Eva Czemerys</a>: Giulia</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Maurizio_Bonuglia&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Maurizio Bonuglia (page does not exist)">Maurizio Bonuglia</a>: Don Giorgio</li>
</ul>
